WEBVTT

00:08.458 --> 00:11.236
MAN: You got anything you
want to say to your parents?

00:11.237 --> 00:13.077
CHESTER: My parents are dead.

00:15.074 --> 00:16.791
[GUNSHOT]

00:16.792 --> 00:18.267
I have a brother.

00:19.437 --> 00:20.762
Stay.

00:20.763 --> 00:21.780
Here?

00:21.781 --> 00:23.881
My family, um...

00:23.882 --> 00:25.626
There's a lot of work.

00:25.627 --> 00:26.960
- [GUNSHOT]
- [SCREAMS]

00:26.961 --> 00:29.145
Some dogs you just have to put down.

00:29.146 --> 00:31.439
It's safer this way.

00:31.440 --> 00:32.799
Trust me.

00:32.800 --> 00:38.204
♪♪

00:39.406 --> 00:42.084
[WIND WHISTLING]

00:42.085 --> 00:44.627
[♪♪]

00:46.000 --> 00:52.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:53.078 --> 00:56.222
[WINDMILL SQUEAKING]

01:07.018 --> 01:10.111
[WIND WHISTLING]

01:25.844 --> 01:28.863
I thought you were leaving today.

01:28.864 --> 01:31.991
Abuela asked me to
stay a couple more days

01:31.992 --> 01:34.535
to dig up a garden for her.

01:34.536 --> 01:36.496
And last week she asked you

01:36.497 --> 01:38.764
to stay just long
enough to patch the roof.

01:49.118 --> 01:50.276
Do you want me to leave?

01:51.519 --> 01:53.052
No.

01:53.053 --> 01:54.333
No, no, of course not.

01:57.856 --> 01:59.022
I don't know what I want.

02:09.662 --> 02:10.737
A couple of days.

02:10.738 --> 02:12.663
Then I'll be out of your hair.

02:23.241 --> 02:25.634
[HOE BITING DIRT]

02:32.292 --> 02:35.042
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

02:44.864 --> 02:46.011
<i>Hola.</i>

02:52.285 --> 02:56.013
[TALKING QUIETLY IN SPANISH]

03:06.052 --> 03:07.301
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

03:14.293 --> 03:15.376
Here.

03:15.377 --> 03:18.020
Abuela's worried you'll be cold.

03:20.566 --> 03:21.774
Thank you.

03:25.237 --> 03:26.517
Any luck?

03:29.599 --> 03:31.475
Nothing yet.

03:31.476 --> 03:34.320
I wrote letters to all the camps,

03:34.321 --> 03:38.566
but... if the courts shut them down,

03:38.567 --> 03:40.447
I don't think I'll ever find him.

03:42.162 --> 03:44.122
At least your parents could go home.

03:50.421 --> 03:51.503
I'll leave you alone.

03:54.313 --> 03:55.313
You could stay.

03:59.171 --> 04:01.230
If you wanted.

04:26.156 --> 04:28.657
Being out here,

04:28.658 --> 04:31.160
it reminds me...

04:31.161 --> 04:33.074
of all those things I said.

04:36.049 --> 04:37.391
The house.

04:39.219 --> 04:40.602
The acre.

04:42.672 --> 04:44.552
You must've thought I was crazy.

04:47.969 --> 04:49.319
No.

04:52.658 --> 04:53.658
I never did.

05:18.408 --> 05:21.208
[♪♪]

05:21.209 --> 05:23.209
<font color="#a4290b">♪ The Terror: Infamy 2x08 ♪</font>
<font color="#cb4b4b">My Sweet Boy</font>

05:55.035 --> 05:58.680
[SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

06:24.274 --> 06:25.541
Next!

06:30.497 --> 06:31.891
Where's Major Bowen?

06:31.892 --> 06:34.092
He was called to Washington, DC.

06:34.093 --> 06:35.334
Very suddenly.

06:35.335 --> 06:36.933
He seemed concerned.

06:36.934 --> 06:38.724
He may be away for a while.

06:39.789 --> 06:42.675
Who is your sponsor, Corbett Delaney?

06:42.676 --> 06:46.164
He's the owner of the
California Canning Company.

06:46.165 --> 06:48.014
I'll be his gardener.

06:48.015 --> 06:49.295
Can you garden?

06:50.517 --> 06:51.800
Yes.

06:51.801 --> 06:52.801
Very well.

06:56.690 --> 06:57.857
Your reparation.

06:57.858 --> 07:00.325
For your return.

07:04.147 --> 07:06.124
Twenty-five dollars...

07:06.125 --> 07:08.200
Apiece.

07:08.201 --> 07:09.409
And a ticket home.

07:13.040 --> 07:14.506
Good luck to you.

07:17.493 --> 07:18.773
Next!

07:23.383 --> 07:25.600
[QUIET CONVERSATIONS]

07:34.425 --> 07:36.116
So when are we going to process

07:36.117 --> 07:37.822
your Leave of Camp papers?

07:37.823 --> 07:39.295
I don't know yet.

07:39.296 --> 07:41.016
I don't have a job lined up.

07:41.017 --> 07:43.018
And with Major Bowen
gone to Washington, I...

07:43.019 --> 07:44.971
The Major came back today.

07:44.972 --> 07:46.021
He did?

07:46.022 --> 07:47.239
[BOWEN]: <i>Konnichiw.</i>

07:47.240 --> 07:49.280
Well, as a matter of fact, there he is.

07:51.244 --> 07:53.362
George.

07:53.363 --> 07:54.413
Miss Yoshida.

07:54.414 --> 07:56.916
How was Washington, sir?

07:56.917 --> 07:58.918
Usual routine.

07:58.919 --> 08:00.086
Never thought I'd say it,

08:00.087 --> 08:02.207
but I kinda missed the
cooking around here.

08:09.596 --> 08:11.897
Swipe a little plate from you?

08:13.100 --> 08:14.107
Thanks very much.

08:18.054 --> 08:20.655
[ROOSTER CROWING]

08:23.610 --> 08:25.452
[ROOSTER CROWING]

08:38.958 --> 08:40.717
[CHESTER SIGHS] It's still early.

08:40.719 --> 08:41.961
Shh.

08:41.962 --> 08:44.130
Abuela will wake up any second.

08:44.131 --> 08:45.280
If she catches us...

08:45.281 --> 08:47.466
Luz... it's been weeks.

08:47.467 --> 08:48.802
How long are we going to pretend

08:48.803 --> 08:50.728
she doesn't know?

08:50.729 --> 08:53.255
She doesn't know.

08:53.256 --> 08:55.176
And unless you have a better idea...

08:57.978 --> 09:01.196
Actually... I do.

09:02.649 --> 09:05.724
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

09:24.154 --> 09:25.154
[ALL]: Amen.

09:36.183 --> 09:38.066
[APPLAUSE]

09:47.527 --> 09:48.527
[FLASHBULB POPPING]

09:56.236 --> 09:57.236
[FLASHBULB POPPING]

10:00.707 --> 10:02.340
Doña Maria.

10:27.326 --> 10:30.076
[BONES CRACKING]

10:35.908 --> 10:37.168
- [APPLAUSE]
- Walt!

10:37.169 --> 10:38.543
Welcome home, Walt.

10:39.862 --> 10:41.521
[BOWEN]: 442nd Infantry.

10:41.522 --> 10:42.915
All Japanese.

10:42.916 --> 10:45.867
More came from this
center than any other.

10:45.868 --> 10:47.788
We're not like the other outfits.

10:49.080 --> 10:51.139
We build patriots.

10:54.094 --> 10:55.928
I will get your bed ready.

10:55.929 --> 10:57.312
Thank you, <i>okasan.</i>

11:02.269 --> 11:03.944
Hey, hi, so...

11:08.508 --> 11:09.700
Did you get my letter?

11:09.701 --> 11:10.901
I got the gist.

11:12.270 --> 11:13.896
Look, um, I'm sorry about Ken,

11:13.897 --> 11:16.282
but you shouldn't have sent
that tape to Washington.

11:16.283 --> 11:20.452
Well, Bowen's back, acting
as if nothing's wrong,

11:20.453 --> 11:21.809
so apparently they never even got it.

11:21.810 --> 11:22.872
Amy, you know, a guy like that,

11:22.873 --> 11:24.290
the rules don't apply to him.

11:24.291 --> 11:25.626
If someone in his circle
found out what you did...

11:25.627 --> 11:27.784
[BOWEN]: It's an honor to have
you back, Lieutenant Yoshida.

11:27.785 --> 11:30.388
It's been a rough couple
of months around here.

11:30.389 --> 11:31.955
Your visit is what the doctor ordered.

11:31.956 --> 11:34.209
We're all so proud of you.

11:34.210 --> 11:35.735
Isn't that right, Sis?

11:35.736 --> 11:37.085
Absolutely.

11:37.086 --> 11:38.304
[BOWEN]: Well, come on!

11:38.305 --> 11:39.305
Tell me how you been!

11:39.306 --> 11:41.924
Uh, I've been great, sir.

11:41.925 --> 11:43.401
Just drumming up some new recruits.

11:43.402 --> 11:45.683
[BOWEN]: Well, we've got
some eager young men for you.

11:49.766 --> 11:51.324
[DISHES BEING STACKED]

11:53.486 --> 11:55.312
It was a beautiful service.

11:55.313 --> 11:58.181
I wish we could've held
it in a proper church,

11:58.182 --> 11:59.912
with more family.

11:59.913 --> 12:01.230
From both sides.

12:02.111 --> 12:03.662
It's better this way, <i>mijo.</i>

12:03.663 --> 12:05.614
The fewer people who know you're here,

12:05.615 --> 12:07.215
the better it is for everyone.

12:09.094 --> 12:10.994
[VEHICLE APPROACHING]

12:10.995 --> 12:11.995
[VEHICLE STOPPING]

12:15.675 --> 12:16.842
<i>Policia?</i>

12:16.843 --> 12:18.143
At this hour?

12:22.849 --> 12:24.016
Chester, go.

12:24.017 --> 12:25.167
Luz...

12:25.168 --> 12:27.019
[ABUELA]: Do what she says. Hurry. Go.

12:27.020 --> 12:28.520
Close the door. Go.

12:28.521 --> 12:29.805
Go.

12:29.806 --> 12:31.357
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

12:31.358 --> 12:32.532
Go.

12:36.288 --> 12:37.288
[OPENING DOOR]

12:39.199 --> 12:41.292
Good evening, ma'am.

12:41.293 --> 12:43.127
Aguayo County sheriffs.

12:43.128 --> 12:46.012
Sorry to bother you so
late. May we come in?

12:57.375 --> 12:59.385
[ABUELA]: There must
be some kind of mistake!

12:59.386 --> 13:01.770
[FOOTSTEPS]

13:07.510 --> 13:08.510
[BREATHING SHAKILY]

13:12.275 --> 13:13.275
What is it?

13:14.600 --> 13:17.227
My father's missing.

13:17.228 --> 13:19.079
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

13:21.858 --> 13:23.575
[CHESTER]: No one saw anything?

13:23.576 --> 13:24.901
[LUZ]: Nothing.

13:24.902 --> 13:25.944
[ABUELA BEGINNING TO PRAY]

13:25.945 --> 13:27.865
And all I left for him was a note.

13:32.585 --> 13:34.753
Abuela?

13:34.754 --> 13:36.038
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

13:36.039 --> 13:39.190
Your father was not
one to just disappear.

13:39.191 --> 13:42.196
He's always responsible, punctual.

13:42.197 --> 13:43.406
You know that.

13:45.432 --> 13:47.049
[LUZ]: No one knows what happened.

13:47.050 --> 13:49.259
He could still be alive.

13:49.260 --> 13:50.469
There is only one way

13:50.470 --> 13:53.405
to know for sure if he has crossed over.

13:53.406 --> 13:54.956
Abuela, no.

13:59.387 --> 14:00.647
What is she talking about?

14:04.901 --> 14:07.286
She's a <i>curandera.</i>

14:07.287 --> 14:10.122
It's a very old magic.

14:10.123 --> 14:11.643
My family believes in it.

14:12.658 --> 14:13.917
Do you believe in it?

14:18.403 --> 14:20.224
I believe...

14:20.225 --> 14:21.374
there's more to the world

14:21.375 --> 14:24.185
than any of us will ever understand.

14:30.810 --> 14:32.803
Does this mean you
can speak to the dead?

14:32.804 --> 14:34.271
No.

14:34.272 --> 14:36.338
But we can discover

14:36.339 --> 14:39.151
if someone's spirit is
still among the living.

14:39.152 --> 14:42.321
It's an old belief

14:42.322 --> 14:43.822
that when a person passes on,

14:43.823 --> 14:45.324
there's some part of their spirit

14:45.325 --> 14:48.827
that remains in their
bones, in their hair...

14:48.828 --> 14:50.411
In pictures as well.

14:52.339 --> 14:54.781
An image captures a
moment in a spirit's life.

14:54.782 --> 14:56.473
The <i>curanderismo</i> can take us

14:56.474 --> 14:59.663
to where Bartolo sat when
he took this picture...

14:59.664 --> 15:03.175
but only if he is dead.

15:03.176 --> 15:05.010
If it fails,

15:05.011 --> 15:08.171
then we know he is still alive.

15:08.172 --> 15:10.231
But none of us are going to do it.

15:11.180 --> 15:12.262
Why not?

15:12.263 --> 15:14.564
<i>Mijo,</i> we can use the magic,

15:14.565 --> 15:16.139
but we can't control it.

15:16.140 --> 15:18.809
Some who've used it to
cross over never return.

15:19.451 --> 15:22.335
Others... never want to.

15:25.031 --> 15:26.356
There must be a mistake.

15:26.357 --> 15:27.707
My father is alive.

15:27.708 --> 15:29.517
He can't just disappear like this.

15:32.539 --> 15:35.157
You believe that, don't you?

15:35.158 --> 15:37.225
I hope he's still alive.

15:39.471 --> 15:41.830
But...

15:41.831 --> 15:42.831
But what?

15:45.885 --> 15:48.479
The <i>curanderismo,</i>

15:48.480 --> 15:49.896
this magic...

15:57.183 --> 15:58.183
I want to try it.

16:01.067 --> 16:04.185
All right, next.

16:04.186 --> 16:05.466
What's your name?

16:06.239 --> 16:09.408
The 442 is the finest
regiment in the US Army.

16:09.409 --> 16:11.243
Are you ready to help us win this war?

16:11.244 --> 16:13.028
Yes, sir.

16:13.029 --> 16:15.005
Then we're happy to have you.

16:15.006 --> 16:16.881
Now, get to your physical, soldier.

16:20.870 --> 16:22.579
Here you go.

16:22.580 --> 16:24.372
You've been making
me coffee for so long,

16:24.373 --> 16:26.773
I figured I'd return the favor.

16:28.085 --> 16:29.878
It's not going to drink itself.

16:29.879 --> 16:32.296
Thank you. It's still a bit hot.

16:34.267 --> 16:35.751
Oh, um...

16:35.752 --> 16:38.030
have you found a sponsor
yet so you can be released?

16:38.031 --> 16:39.438
No.

16:39.439 --> 16:40.439
Not yet.

16:43.059 --> 16:44.535
Let me see what I can do about that.

16:44.536 --> 16:45.899
It's the least I can do.

16:48.814 --> 16:51.249
I'm sure that's cool
enough to drink now.

16:52.443 --> 16:53.751
You enjoy.

17:06.132 --> 17:07.612
[TOSHIRO]: Walt.

17:08.867 --> 17:09.894
Toshiro.

17:09.895 --> 17:10.895
What are you doing here?

17:10.896 --> 17:12.471
I turned 18 last month.

17:12.472 --> 17:14.872
I'm old enough to enlist.

17:18.403 --> 17:19.403
Listen, um...

17:21.740 --> 17:24.983
anywhere that's too dangerous
to send the white soldiers,

17:24.983 --> 17:27.578
they send us instead.

17:27.579 --> 17:28.971
The guys in my unit

17:28.972 --> 17:33.417
are, uh, dying faster
than they can be replaced.

17:33.418 --> 17:34.626
That's why I'm here.

17:36.278 --> 17:37.654
You tell all the recruits that?

17:37.655 --> 17:41.907
Toshiro, with all respect,
this isn't for you.

17:44.337 --> 17:46.505
I know all of you act
like I'm still a kid,

17:46.506 --> 17:49.174
but all I've seen is
people die around me...

17:49.175 --> 17:53.345
my mom, my dad, my friends.

17:53.346 --> 17:55.506
I graduated high school
in a goddamned prison.

17:56.882 --> 17:57.957
So help me,

17:57.958 --> 18:00.025
but all I want to do is kill.

18:03.392 --> 18:06.268
If you won't take my form,
I'll go find someone who will.

18:24.430 --> 18:26.369
Ah, Miss Yoshida, there you are.

18:26.370 --> 18:28.547
I need you to come with me.

18:28.548 --> 18:30.474
I'm sorry?

18:30.475 --> 18:31.678
Supply truck broke down

18:31.679 --> 18:34.052
with all the drinks and party favors.

18:34.053 --> 18:35.461
I don't think I understand.

18:35.462 --> 18:37.005
We're throwing a bit of a shindig,

18:37.006 --> 18:38.173
but it's kind of top secret.

18:38.174 --> 18:40.425
We're celebrating the
homecoming of your brother,

18:40.426 --> 18:42.486
and, well, folks like you

18:42.487 --> 18:44.047
who are getting to leave the camp.

18:44.664 --> 18:46.142
I spoke to my old Lieutenant Colonel

18:46.143 --> 18:47.167
in Long Beach,

18:47.168 --> 18:49.159
and he needs a new secretary.

18:49.160 --> 18:51.392
He's willing to sponsor
you for your release.

18:51.393 --> 18:53.688
Oh, uh, thank you. I, um...

18:53.689 --> 18:57.292
But we can't have a party
without the proper supplies.

19:10.089 --> 19:11.519
Sometimes I like to drive

19:11.520 --> 19:12.758
just for the peace and quiet.

19:12.759 --> 19:16.094
For hours at a time.

19:16.095 --> 19:18.048
Nothing or no one around for miles.

19:18.049 --> 19:20.982
Just me and the clean, fresh air.

19:22.435 --> 19:23.715
[SIGHING]

19:31.202 --> 19:33.445
How much further?

19:33.446 --> 19:35.304
Not sure.

19:35.305 --> 19:37.521
Been out here for three years,

19:37.522 --> 19:39.209
and I still don't know my way around.

19:39.210 --> 19:40.210
[LAUGHING]

19:43.806 --> 19:44.882
[HONKING HORN]

19:44.883 --> 19:46.216
There you go.

19:46.217 --> 19:47.394
Right up there.

19:47.395 --> 19:49.093
[HONKING]

19:53.800 --> 19:55.080
[GEARING DOWN]

19:58.420 --> 20:00.138
[APPLYING BRAKES]

20:00.139 --> 20:01.172
[TURNING OFF ENGINE]

20:01.173 --> 20:02.941
Amy! Major Bowen!

20:02.942 --> 20:04.168
Thanks.

20:04.169 --> 20:06.265
We would have been out here all night.

20:06.266 --> 20:08.795
Come on, fellas. Let's get
these supplies unloaded.

20:08.796 --> 20:11.115
We're gonna have a party tonight!

20:15.822 --> 20:18.323
[ABUELA]: Taking this journey,

20:18.324 --> 20:22.419
carrying the eye of your
spirit to the other side,

20:22.420 --> 20:26.665
you may feel like you
are dying yourself.

20:26.666 --> 20:28.950
[CHESTER]: I understand.

20:28.951 --> 20:31.494
[LUZ]: My husband has little
regard for his own life.

20:31.495 --> 20:34.100
If I can go to my brother,

20:34.101 --> 20:35.347
meet him...

20:35.348 --> 20:36.784
That would mean he's dead.

20:38.460 --> 20:39.740
But at least I'd know.

20:40.847 --> 20:43.181
If you meet your brother,

20:43.182 --> 20:45.275
it will be him

20:45.276 --> 20:47.519
at the moment of this picture.

20:47.520 --> 20:48.797
A little boy.

20:48.798 --> 20:52.156
He will not know he is dead.

21:06.114 --> 21:08.072
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

22:14.056 --> 22:16.867
Look for your brother, Jirou.

22:16.868 --> 22:20.542
Rejoice if you do not find him.

22:22.040 --> 22:25.424
Grieve, grieve if you do.

22:57.182 --> 22:58.199
Amen.

23:09.587 --> 23:11.212
[EXHALING IN RELIEF]

23:25.461 --> 23:27.962
[STARTLING]

23:27.963 --> 23:28.963
Jirou...

23:32.634 --> 23:33.634
Do I know you?

23:37.615 --> 23:40.450
No.

23:40.451 --> 23:42.076
I don't think you do.

23:44.971 --> 23:45.971
Are you Jirou?

23:47.983 --> 23:49.263
How do you know?

23:52.038 --> 23:53.545
Lucky guess, I suppose.

23:56.835 --> 23:59.694
My name is...

23:59.695 --> 24:00.695
Taizo.

24:01.973 --> 24:04.253
The nuns said that
was my brother's name.

24:07.960 --> 24:10.144
Do you know what happened to him?

24:10.145 --> 24:14.151
They said a family took
him when we were babies,

24:14.152 --> 24:18.155
when I was still at the hospital.

24:18.156 --> 24:20.214
I guess he was just luckier.

24:26.021 --> 24:30.408
Hey, do you like baseball?

24:30.409 --> 24:32.410
Do the other kids play with you?

24:32.411 --> 24:34.746
They think I'm cursed.

24:34.747 --> 24:37.674
And I'm always sick.

24:37.675 --> 24:40.635
The nuns say I'll get
better if I pray enough.

24:45.091 --> 24:46.891
I'm sure you will.

24:48.260 --> 24:50.378
Then you'll get to play.

24:50.379 --> 24:52.547
I'll never get to play.

24:52.548 --> 24:54.565
I can't even throw the ball right.

24:58.771 --> 24:59.971
I bet you can.

25:01.140 --> 25:02.573
Show me.

25:13.452 --> 25:15.620
First pitch.

25:15.621 --> 25:17.401
Lou Gehrig's up to bat.

25:20.626 --> 25:21.718
Swing and a miss.

25:21.719 --> 25:23.019
Strike one.

25:27.569 --> 25:30.646
Good, Jirou... good.

25:35.122 --> 25:36.363
Strike two.

25:36.364 --> 25:37.747
[LAUGHING]

25:38.310 --> 25:40.595
[GASPING]

25:40.596 --> 25:42.147
[GASPING]

25:42.148 --> 25:44.531
What's happening?

25:47.319 --> 25:48.936
Taizo?

25:48.937 --> 25:50.989
[GASPING]

25:50.990 --> 25:51.990
Are you okay?

25:53.576 --> 25:54.650
Chester! Wake up!

25:54.651 --> 25:55.714
No!

26:16.465 --> 26:17.465
[GASPING]

26:20.135 --> 26:21.135
[HIGH VOICE]

26:24.014 --> 26:26.157
[SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

26:41.965 --> 26:42.965
Jirou...

26:44.469 --> 26:47.178
I'm... your mother.

26:50.216 --> 26:52.433
[SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

27:05.501 --> 27:07.968
I... I don't understand.

27:32.298 --> 27:34.569
You... you're hurting me.

27:36.595 --> 27:38.479
[JIROU CRYING OUT]

27:43.602 --> 27:46.153
[JIROU FIGHTING FOR BREATH]

27:48.107 --> 27:49.823
[JIROU CRIES OUT]

27:50.943 --> 27:54.779
[CHESTER GASPING]

27:54.780 --> 27:55.872
I felt her.

27:55.873 --> 27:57.295
She's here.

27:57.296 --> 27:58.562
Who is here?

28:03.789 --> 28:05.422
Oh, God.

28:07.284 --> 28:09.074
- No!
- ... Chester, wait! Wait!

28:09.075 --> 28:10.075
Jirou!

28:13.290 --> 28:14.598
Jirou!

28:16.802 --> 28:17.802
That wind...

28:20.398 --> 28:23.233
That was you, wasn't it?

28:23.234 --> 28:26.093
You were always with me.

28:26.094 --> 28:27.662
And now you're gone.

28:30.649 --> 28:33.284
[GASPING]

28:37.272 --> 28:38.472
I saw Jirou.

28:39.750 --> 28:42.159
I led her there, and she took him.

28:43.588 --> 28:46.497
She took my brother.

28:46.498 --> 28:48.007
Who took him?

28:50.873 --> 28:52.932
My... mother.

28:55.222 --> 28:56.730
Yuko.

28:57.843 --> 29:03.964
♪ <i>I dream of you ♪</i>

29:03.965 --> 29:09.946
♪ <i>More than you dream I do ♪</i>

29:09.947 --> 29:16.977
♪ <i>How can I prove to you ♪</i>

29:16.978 --> 29:19.747
♪ <i>This love is real ♪</i>

29:23.702 --> 29:29.424
♪ <i>You're mean to me ♪</i>

29:29.425 --> 29:35.496
♪ <i>More than you mean to be ♪</i>

29:35.497 --> 29:41.168
♪ <i>You just can't seem to see ♪</i>

29:41.169 --> 29:42.845
♪ <i>The way I feel ♪</i>

29:42.846 --> 29:44.839
I think this is the first time
I've seen you relax

29:44.840 --> 29:47.558
since I've been back.

29:47.559 --> 29:50.010
I was so certain Bowen
was out to get me.

29:50.011 --> 29:51.896
What changed your mind?

29:51.897 --> 29:53.947
This, I guess.

29:55.647 --> 29:58.431
I didn't think he was really
going to throw a party.

29:59.405 --> 30:00.704
For us.

30:06.504 --> 30:09.005
[SIGHING]

30:09.006 --> 30:12.090
Ken wanted this day to come so bad.

30:15.912 --> 30:17.472
But this...

30:17.473 --> 30:19.924
he would've found it all so dumb.

30:19.925 --> 30:21.393
[CHUCKLING]

30:21.394 --> 30:22.601
Yeah.

30:26.265 --> 30:28.099
Yeah, I bet he'd really roll his eyes

30:28.100 --> 30:30.435
if he saw you dance
with your stupid brother.

30:30.436 --> 30:31.652
[LAUGHING]

30:34.055 --> 30:37.658
♪ <i>I dream of you ♪</i>

30:47.277 --> 30:49.620
[PARTY NOISE IN THE DISTANCE]

30:49.621 --> 30:52.756
[RAIN FALLING]

31:20.152 --> 31:22.161
Miss Yoshida...

31:23.146 --> 31:24.872
You've had too much to drink.

31:43.542 --> 31:46.102
When I was a young officer,

31:46.103 --> 31:48.129
I was taught discipline.

31:48.130 --> 31:49.952
Watch what you do.

31:51.517 --> 31:52.775
What you say.

31:54.520 --> 31:55.914
What you eat...

31:58.140 --> 31:59.857
and what you drink.

31:59.858 --> 32:00.858
[CUP CLATTERING]

32:00.859 --> 32:02.493
[WHIMPERING]

32:04.530 --> 32:07.123
But most of all,

32:07.124 --> 32:09.249
they taught me to watch who I trusted.

32:12.696 --> 32:16.490
I will never forget

32:16.491 --> 32:19.493
the day you and your mother
walked into my office.

32:21.380 --> 32:23.473
She sat down,

32:23.474 --> 32:26.217
and looked me right in the eye,

32:26.218 --> 32:27.368
and she said

32:27.369 --> 32:30.888
that you wanted to help your country

32:30.889 --> 32:33.891
during a time of war.

32:33.892 --> 32:37.061
And I believed her.

32:37.062 --> 32:38.946
And I believed you.

32:40.725 --> 32:41.732
And then...

32:41.733 --> 32:42.866
[WHIMPERING]

32:49.241 --> 32:50.908
[TURNING TAPE MACHINE ON]

32:50.909 --> 32:53.744
[BOWEN ON RECORDING]: <i>Some
dogs you just have to put down.</i>

32:53.745 --> 32:55.079
<i>It's safer this way.</i>

32:55.080 --> 32:57.582
<i>Trust me.</i>

32:57.583 --> 32:59.476
<i>Don't be so hard on yourself.</i>

32:59.477 --> 33:01.118
<i>He didn't leave you any more choice</i>

33:01.119 --> 33:02.345
<i>than he left me.</i>

33:02.346 --> 33:04.755
<i>Oh...</i>

33:04.756 --> 33:07.091
<i>[SIGHING]</i>

33:07.092 --> 33:09.726
<i>I knew you were one of the good ones.</i>

33:11.296 --> 33:13.022
<i>I always trusted you.</i>

33:13.023 --> 33:14.439
[TURNING TAPE MACHINE OFF]

33:17.695 --> 33:19.720
The WRA did receive the reel,

33:19.721 --> 33:23.748
sent anonymously, just as you planned.

33:26.061 --> 33:27.778
But thankfully,

33:27.779 --> 33:32.041
an old buddy of mine from
my officer training days

33:32.042 --> 33:33.901
was in the office when it came in,

33:33.902 --> 33:38.263
and thankfully, that
buddy's a loyal man.

33:40.292 --> 33:42.301
A patriot, if you will.

33:45.080 --> 33:47.056
[SIGHING]

33:47.057 --> 33:50.393
Now, Miss Yoshida,

33:50.394 --> 33:52.753
if you'll just control yourself,

33:52.754 --> 33:56.423
perhaps we can discuss
the current situation

33:56.424 --> 33:58.210
and how we're going to handle it

34:00.070 --> 34:02.390
and our potential future together.

34:13.775 --> 34:15.873
[SCREAMING] Help! Help me!

34:15.873 --> 34:17.507
I gave you a chance!

34:20.666 --> 34:22.616
Go ahead and scream all you want!

34:22.617 --> 34:25.503
Nobody can hear you.

34:25.504 --> 34:27.672
We're underground.

34:27.672 --> 34:29.674
In Block 36.

34:29.675 --> 34:32.255
They're all the way across camp.

34:33.178 --> 34:35.312
They can't hear shit.

34:37.181 --> 34:38.181
And to think...

34:39.884 --> 34:42.018
I was this close to regretting

34:42.020 --> 34:44.540
that this camp ever existed.

34:45.974 --> 34:48.025
Goddamn it!

34:48.025 --> 34:49.293
Try to maintain

34:49.295 --> 34:50.678
a functioning electrical grid

34:50.679 --> 34:52.639
out here in the middle of nowhere...

34:56.868 --> 34:57.868
And then...

34:59.296 --> 35:01.146
as you were all softening me up,

35:01.147 --> 35:03.490
you showed your true colors.

35:03.491 --> 35:06.327
Nakayama attacking my MPs.

35:06.328 --> 35:10.430
Ken, O Lover Boy, takes me hostage...

35:12.050 --> 35:13.718
You miss him, don't you?

35:13.719 --> 35:15.805
You miss his touch.

35:16.555 --> 35:17.713
[SPITTING]

35:17.714 --> 35:18.714
Go to hell!

35:27.015 --> 35:30.535
I really liked you, Amy.

35:30.536 --> 35:31.569
Hell...

35:31.570 --> 35:33.404
[WHIMPERING]

35:33.405 --> 35:34.538
I still do.

35:35.365 --> 35:36.407
[SNAPPING]

35:36.408 --> 35:38.075
[SCREAMING]

35:38.076 --> 35:40.127
[SOBBING]

35:46.201 --> 35:48.301
[CRYING]

35:56.127 --> 35:58.079
[CHESTER]: She said she
wanted me and my brother

35:58.080 --> 35:59.338
to live with her

35:59.339 --> 36:01.440
in her perfect world.

36:02.458 --> 36:04.385
Your mother's spirit is following you?

36:04.386 --> 36:06.604
She tracked me to Guadalcanal,

36:06.605 --> 36:09.515
and now she's here.

36:09.516 --> 36:11.350
You knew this, and you kept it from me?

36:11.351 --> 36:12.893
Even when my father was missing?

36:12.894 --> 36:15.538
Luz, it's been two years.

36:15.539 --> 36:18.541
We thought we destroyed her at the camp.

36:18.542 --> 36:20.451
I thought it was all over.

36:20.452 --> 36:21.843
I thought we were over.

36:22.848 --> 36:24.080
After all you'd been through,

36:24.081 --> 36:25.589
how could I tell you?

36:29.244 --> 36:30.786
Yuko was my midwife.

36:30.787 --> 36:33.556
She was kind to me.

36:33.557 --> 36:35.797
Why would a spirit do that?

36:36.870 --> 36:38.170
I don't know.

36:40.549 --> 36:41.732
Did she kill my father?

36:44.142 --> 36:45.810
It's...

36:45.811 --> 36:47.311
it's possible.

36:49.106 --> 36:50.781
The wedding photos.

37:02.419 --> 37:04.736
This blur.

37:04.737 --> 37:06.449
It's a sign that Yuko's spirit

37:06.450 --> 37:07.703
is controlling someone.

37:07.704 --> 37:09.327
Possessing them.

37:11.182 --> 37:12.502
Yuko was at the wedding?

37:14.264 --> 37:17.148
Chester, this is Doña Maria.

37:19.794 --> 37:22.646
When's the last time
either of you saw her?

37:49.324 --> 37:50.799
[DOOR SQUEAKING]

37:55.955 --> 37:57.013
[CLOSING DOOR]

37:59.375 --> 38:01.184
Doña Maria?

38:03.171 --> 38:04.429
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

38:30.248 --> 38:31.248
[GASPING]

38:47.507 --> 38:49.067
People are going to notice I'm missing.

38:50.113 --> 38:53.465
My friends, my family,
they'll come looking for me.

38:56.608 --> 38:58.783
And in a few days, I'm
sure they'll find you.

39:04.783 --> 39:07.709
I swear to God this place is haunted.

39:14.885 --> 39:17.127
Of course it's haunted.

39:17.128 --> 39:18.762
All the Japanese know that.

39:19.747 --> 39:21.224
[SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

39:21.225 --> 39:22.729
What are you mumbling about?

39:22.730 --> 39:25.419
The <i>yurei.</i>

39:25.420 --> 39:27.128
The wandering spirit.

39:29.590 --> 39:32.503
You've seen her, haven't you?

39:32.504 --> 39:34.814
What did Yuko do to you?

39:36.907 --> 39:39.149
Yuko? That's her name?

39:39.150 --> 39:42.411
She's from my island.

39:42.412 --> 39:43.821
I can tell you all about her.

39:44.656 --> 39:45.997
Shut up. You're lying.

39:48.585 --> 39:51.002
They say she likes dark, hidden places.

39:52.589 --> 39:54.286
Should I call Yuko down here?

39:54.287 --> 39:56.667
Or maybe just let her possess one of us.

39:56.668 --> 39:58.928
[COCKING GUN]

39:58.929 --> 40:01.121
You shut your mouth.

40:01.122 --> 40:04.527
I'm not falling for any of
your voodoo bullshit.

40:06.103 --> 40:08.771
Goddamn this camp.

40:08.772 --> 40:10.063
[SIGHING]

40:13.468 --> 40:14.468
[SCREAMING]

40:16.637 --> 40:18.614
[GROANING]

40:18.615 --> 40:19.948
[SCREAMING]

40:27.815 --> 40:29.775
[STRUGGLING]

40:29.776 --> 40:32.127
[GASPING FOR AIR]

40:33.613 --> 40:35.588
[BOWEN CHOKING]

40:37.375 --> 40:39.467
[GASPING]

40:41.305 --> 40:43.455
[SPLUTTERING]

40:43.456 --> 40:44.931
[FALLING SILENT]

40:54.509 --> 40:56.768
[DOOR OPENING]

40:56.769 --> 40:57.844
[DOOR CLOSING]

40:57.845 --> 40:58.845
[RUNNING FOOTSTEPS]

41:02.567 --> 41:03.809
Doña Maria's dead.

41:03.810 --> 41:06.036
Yuko killed her.

41:10.650 --> 41:12.751
She was holding this.

41:19.325 --> 41:21.827
Yuko...

41:21.828 --> 41:23.136
she knows.

41:25.206 --> 41:26.222
She knows what?

41:27.467 --> 41:29.559
She's not here for you.

41:32.672 --> 41:34.431
I'm pregnant.

41:34.432 --> 41:37.400
She's come for our baby.

41:41.389 --> 41:43.323
[BIRDS SINGING]

41:44.609 --> 41:46.701
[INSECTS BUZZING]

41:57.047 --> 41:58.746
[SPEAKING IN JAPANESE]

42:47.821 --> 42:49.620
[♪♪]

